column1: Table 4a.  Reported Voting and Registration of the Total Voting-Age Population, by Sex, Race, and Hispanic Origin, for States: November 2000
Note:  The symbol B means that the base is too small to show the derived measure.
N-H represents Non-Hispanic.  API includes Asian and Pacific Islander.
Hispanics may be of any race.
-  Represents zero or rounds to zero.
